Subject: Re: [VB] shift rod tube

Look at Kelly's site www.metwiz.com, he has some pictures of a front
crossmember that he replaced. His solution was to cut the crossmember so
that he didn't incur alignment problems with the shift tube.
His site is a real treasure of information if you're doing a restoration.
John Flowers
